19/06/2007
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia -- Danish Defence Minister Soren Gade spent the day in Kosovo on Monday (June 18th), and met with the commander of KFOR, Lieutenant General Roland Kather, who reiterated KFOR's determination to maintain a calm and secure environment in Kosovo. Gade also visited Danish troops deployed in northern Kosovo. 
In other news Monday, Kosovo Prime Minister Agim Ceku ruled out new negotiations or changes to UN envoy Martti Ahtisaari's proposal for supervised independence. Ceku warned that "every delay" affects public trust in both domestic and international authorities. (Blic - 19/06/07; RFE, RTK, Telegrafi, Balkanweb, KosovaLive - 18/06/07)
